&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Consultant Haematologist with interests in Paroxysmal Nocturnal Haemoglobinuria (PNH) and Aplastic Anaemia (AA)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;St James’ Hospital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Closing Date: 12 November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Ref: 298-CON-634&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual to fill this new 8PA post within the Clinical Haematology Department at St James’s University Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the National Paroxysmal Nocturnal Haemoglobinuria (PNH) service based at St James’ Hospital which is recognised in the UK and worldwide as leaders in this disease area. There will be particular emphasis in relation to the expanding trials workload and research interests in that area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to contribute actively to the clinical and laboratory PNH and AA service. The successful candidate will participate in the out of hours cover for the PNH Service (support by telephone for patients from throughout the United Kingdom). There is opportunity for the successful candidate to further develop their scientific interest in PNH and related disorders. The clinical trials portfolio is extensive and this post will help support that infrastructure and allow it to further develop. The post holder will be involved in developing, opening and treating patients within clinical trials with the team, as part of their role. The post holder will participate in clinical attending for in-patient care for patients with PNH and AA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant should possess MRCP and FRCPath (or equivalent) and should be included on the Specialist Register or within 6 months of CCT at the time of interview, if currently within a training programme within the UK. In accordance with the consultant appointment regulations, all other categories of doctors must be on the Specialist Register.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consideration will be given to applicants who wish to work full or part time and those wishing to job share.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prospective applicants are encouraged to contact one of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr R J Johnson, Consultant Haematologist &amp; Lead Clinician email address: rodjohnson@nhs.net, contact number 0113 2068417&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr M Griffin, Consultant Haematologist &amp; Clinical Lead of the National PNH NCG Service email address:  m.griffin@nhs.net  , contact number 0113 2068428&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;INTERVIEWS WILL BE HELD VIA ZOOM: Friday 4 December 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you wish to discuss this, or have any queries, please contact Lynn Lindley in Medical Staffing on (0113) 2064895: E Mail Address: LynnLindley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that only electronic applications can be accepted for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
